{"name": "smsactivatepy", "metadata": {"name": "smsactivatepy", "version": "1", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "smsactivatepy is an Python module that provides functions for working with the API sms-activate.org", "upload_time": 1734296647}, "documentation": ["# SMSActivatePy Library\n\nA Python library for interacting with the [SMSActivate API](https://sms-activate.org/api2). This tool allows you to integrate SMS activation services seamlessly into your projects.\n\n## Installation\n\nTo install the library, run the following command:\n\n```sh\npip install smsactivatepy\n```\n\n## Requirements\n\n- `requests`\n- `json`\n\n## Usage Example\n\n```python\nfrom smsactivatepy.api import SMSActivateAPI\n\n# Initialize the API with your key\nsa = SMSActivateAPI(APIKEY)\n\n# Enable debug mode (optional, for troubleshooting)\nsa.debug_mode = True\n```\n\n## Features\n\nThis library provides an interface for accessing the SMSActivate service. You can use it for operations such as:\n- Requesting a virtual phone number\n- Managing SMS activations\n- Checking account balance\n\nDetailed functionality is described in the official [SMSActivate API documentation](https://sms-activate.org/api2).\n\n## Author\n\nDeveloped by Gabriel Lima  \nEmail: [gabrielmrts@yahoo.com](mailto:gabrielmrts@yahoo.com)\n"], "modules": [{"name": "smsactivatepy", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "smsactivatepy.api", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "smsactivatepy.api.SMSActivateAPI", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "smsactivatepy.api.SMSActivateAPI.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "api_key", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns":